By the way,

254
00:13:38,138 --> 00:13:40,453
have you contacted the President?

255
00:13:40,453 --> 00:13:42,172
Oh.

256
00:13:42,172 --> 00:13:44,905
He's probably swamped right now.

257
00:13:45,972 --> 00:13:48,005
I feel terrible since this seems
to have happened because of me.

258
00:13:48,005 --> 00:13:49,605
How could it be because of you?

259
00:13:49,605 --> 00:13:51,838
Please don't think that way.

260
00:13:52,738 --> 00:13:55,938
He's stronger than you think.

261
00:13:55,938 --> 00:13:58,105
He definitely won't crumble
over something like this.

262
00:13:58,105 --> 00:14:00,672
Just trust us and wait a little longer.

263
00:14:00,672 --> 00:14:02,085
Okay,

264
00:14:02,085 --> 00:14:03,269
thanks.

265
00:14:26,105 --> 00:14:30,105
Yes, that level of coverage will be fine.

266
00:14:30,105 --> 00:14:32,138
Understood.

267
00:14:33,772 --> 00:14:35,205
I told you your phone stays off.

268
00:14:35,205 --> 00:14:36,305
Don't turn it on yet.

269
00:14:36,305 --> 00:14:38,638
But shouldn't I contact Hui Won?

270
00:14:38,638 --> 00:14:39,672
She'll keep worrying.

271
00:14:39,672 --> 00:14:41,338
Just for a moment.

272
00:14:41,338 --> 00:14:42,738
The company is currently

273
00:14:42,738 --> 00:14:44,901
handling the defamation case.

274
00:14:44,901 --> 00:14:46,272
Just until then, okay?

275
00:14:46,272 --> 00:14:49,138
Do you also wish
I'd followed Father's advice?

276
00:14:49,805 --> 00:14:52,638
I know it's not completely wrong,

277
00:14:53,538 --> 00:14:55,938
but I'm not sure it's right either.

278
00:14:57,972 --> 00:15:00,038
I know what's holding you back.

279
00:15:00,038 --> 00:15:03,105
But the Chairman didn't say that lightly.

280
00:15:03,105 --> 00:15:05,005
I'm worried about Hui Won too,

281
00:15:05,005 --> 00:15:07,405
but every word you say,

282
00:15:07,405 --> 00:15:09,505
every action you take represents the company.

283
00:15:11,405 --> 00:15:13,205
Think as rationally as possible.

284
00:15:13,205 --> 00:15:14,538
You're good at that.

285
00:15:14,538 --> 00:15:17,505
Judging without being swayed
by emotions or circumstances.

286
00:15:17,505 --> 00:15:19,372
Right now,

287
00:15:20,172 --> 00:15:22,305
that's what will protect you.

288
00:15:34,405 --> 00:15:35,538
Hello.

289
00:15:35,538 --> 00:15:38,138
Yeah, come in. Mi Ran already ordered.

290
00:15:38,138 --> 00:15:39,172
Sit here.

291
00:15:39,172 --> 00:15:40,905
Okay.

292
00:15:41,905 --> 00:15:43,305
Did you hear?

293
00:15:43,305 --> 00:15:47,172
That Taehan Liquor President, Kang Du Jun,
who had a blind date at our place.

294
00:15:47,172 --> 00:15:48,438
It's total chaos.

295
00:15:48,438 --> 00:15:50,305
They say he hit on
every woman at the company.

296
00:15:50,305 --> 00:15:53,305
He went after any woman
he could get his hands on.

297
00:15:53,305 --> 00:15:55,405
No wonder he looked like a player.

298
00:15:55,405 --> 00:15:59,238
He even pressured that pregnant woman
into abortion and paid her off.

299
00:15:59,238 --> 00:16:00,638
What a psycho. Unbelievable.

300
00:16:00,638 --> 00:16:03,438
Who'd drink their beer? It's disgusting.

301
00:16:04,272 --> 00:16:06,438
Excuse me.

302
00:16:06,438 --> 00:16:07,438
Did you see it yourself?

303
00:16:07,438 --> 00:16:10,105
Did you actually see our president
going after every woman

304
00:16:10,105 --> 00:16:11,805
just because she's a woman?

305
00:16:11,805 --> 00:16:13,472
- What the...
- What's it to you?

306
00:16:13,472 --> 00:16:15,572
- Who are you?
- What do you mean?

307
00:16:15,572 --> 00:16:17,372
I'm actually that...

308
00:16:17,372 --> 00:16:19,238
She's that one!

309
00:16:19,238 --> 00:16:21,505
She's the crazy ex in this neighborhood.

310
00:16:21,505 --> 00:16:25,238
When she gets mad, she smashes bottles
and grabs collars. Total chaos.

311
00:16:25,238 --> 00:16:28,272
Don't bother. Just walk away.

312
00:16:29,638 --> 00:16:33,172
Hey, I told you causing trouble
again would be bad.

313
00:16:33,172 --> 00:16:34,905
Come on.

314
00:16:42,072 --> 00:16:43,972
Hotels get guests like that all the time.

315
00:16:43,972 --> 00:16:48,438
Just play dead and avoid them.
That's the smart move.

316
00:16:49,872 --> 00:16:52,138
Wow. I can't believe these words
came out of my mouth.

317
00:16:52,138 --> 00:16:54,138
You've grown up, Hwang Mi Ran.

318
00:16:54,138 --> 00:16:56,772
I know,

319
00:16:56,772 --> 00:16:58,538
but listening to that makes my blood boil.

320
00:16:58,538 --> 00:17:01,705
Oh, so you can't stand hearing
your boyfriend get insulted, huh?

321
00:17:01,705 --> 00:17:02,905
Hey, even so,

322
00:17:02,905 --> 00:17:05,605
what if it gets exposed
because you stepped in?

323
00:17:06,405 --> 00:17:08,138
Actually,

324
00:17:09,038 --> 00:17:12,005
I don't know if staying quiet
is really right.

325
00:17:12,005 --> 00:17:14,238
What if I say I'm the woman
in that tabloid article?

326
00:17:14,238 --> 00:17:16,872
And if I say the President
isn't that kind of person?

327
00:17:16,872 --> 00:17:19,038
Wouldn't that clear up at least
some of the misunderstanding?

328
00:17:19,038 --> 00:17:20,072
Well.

329
00:17:20,072 --> 00:17:21,838
Given the current situation,

330
00:17:21,838 --> 00:17:24,672
would anyone believe it?

331
00:17:24,672 --> 00:17:26,772
What people care about is Kang Du Jun.

332
00:17:26,772 --> 00:17:27,941
People find it entertaining to watch

333
00:17:27,941 --> 00:17:30,572
a rich heir who has everything
fall from grace.

334
00:17:30,572 --> 00:17:33,472
And if it's revealed that you're the woman,

335
00:17:33,472 --> 00:17:37,038
you'll get torn apart too,
are you okay with that?

336
00:17:40,605 --> 00:17:43,505
The President must be looking for
his own way to handle this.

337
00:17:43,505 --> 00:17:47,372
If you step forward unnecessarily,
it might make things worse, so for now,

338
00:17:47,372 --> 00:17:49,372
just focus on yourself and Yeol Mu.

339
00:17:49,372 --> 00:17:51,905
Eat something, even if you have to force it.

340
00:17:51,905 --> 00:17:54,538
You like rolled omelets, right? Try some.

341
00:17:56,238 --> 00:17:57,838
[Multiple tips emerge about Taehan Liquor
President Kang Du Jun's womanizing]

342
00:17:57,838 --> 00:17:58,872
[The ugly double life
of a CEO-turned-ad model]

343
00:17:58,872 --> 00:18:01,445
[Multiple inappropriate relationships
with company employees]

344
00:18:14,105 --> 00:18:16,472
You know who's behind this, don't you?

345
00:18:16,472 --> 00:18:19,038
Your sister-in-law is waiting
for you to make a mistake.

346
00:18:19,038 --> 00:18:20,438
The moment you acknowledge that woman,

347
00:18:20,438 --> 00:18:22,638
it becomes the excuse to bring you down.

348
00:18:22,638 --> 00:18:24,238
For now, do as I say.

349
00:18:24,238 --> 00:18:27,438
Because that's the way
to protect you and her.

350
00:18:58,505 --> 00:19:00,205
Hui Won.

351
00:19:03,605 --> 00:19:05,138
President.

352
00:19:05,138 --> 00:19:09,072
I'm sorry, I couldn't contact you
because my phone was off.

353
00:19:10,672 --> 00:19:12,305
Still,

354
00:19:12,305 --> 00:19:16,538
was it really that hard to send
one text saying you're okay?

355
00:19:21,221 --> 00:19:23,605
You were waiting for my call, weren't you?

356
00:19:23,605 --> 00:19:25,605
I don't know.

357
00:19:28,772 --> 00:19:30,905
I missed you, really.

358
00:19:34,838 --> 00:19:36,538
Me too.

359
00:19:47,172 --> 00:19:48,905
Do you have somewhere to go?

360
00:19:48,905 --> 00:19:52,538
The news said reporters are
even camped out in front of your house.

361
00:19:52,538 --> 00:19:54,338
I need to head back to the office.

362
00:19:54,338 --> 00:19:56,997
- I'll probably be in meetings all night.
- Oh.

363
00:19:58,205 --> 00:19:59,605
Yeah?

364
00:19:59,605 --> 00:20:00,938
You look a little disappointed.

365
00:20:00,938 --> 00:20:03,605
What if I'm not just a little
but very disappointed?

366
00:20:04,472 --> 00:20:07,172
Shall I cancel all the meetings
and everything else?

367
00:20:07,172 --> 00:20:08,438
Don't be ridiculous.

368
00:20:08,438 --> 00:20:10,138
I'm saying this because I'm worried.

369
00:20:10,138 --> 00:20:11,405
I'm really okay.

370
00:20:11,405 --> 00:20:13,505
You don't need to worry about me.

371
00:20:14,972 --> 00:20:18,805
I feel like I shouldn't have recommended
you as the commercial model.

372
00:20:18,805 --> 00:20:23,538
Because of me, you became more exposed,
and now it's even harder for you.

373
00:20:23,538 --> 00:20:26,205
I'll just reveal everything myself.

374
00:20:26,205 --> 00:20:28,672
If I step forward
and say the rumors aren't true,

375
00:20:28,672 --> 00:20:29,905
- then you...
- No.

376
00:20:29,905 --> 00:20:31,838
I don't want that.

377
00:20:31,838 --> 00:20:33,305
The moment it's revealed,

378
00:20:33,305 --> 00:20:35,138
people will say all your achievements

379
00:20:35,138 --> 00:20:37,005
were gained because of me,
and they'll belittle you.

380
00:20:37,005 --> 00:20:39,405
And it might create
even bigger misunderstandings.

381
00:20:39,405 --> 00:20:41,638
I'm looking for a solution now.

382
00:20:41,638 --> 00:20:45,272
Trust me and wait a little longer, okay?

383
00:20:46,572 --> 00:20:48,272
Okay.

384
00:20:51,472 --> 00:20:54,638
The subscriber's phone is turned off.

385
00:20:54,638 --> 00:20:56,972
- Oh, jeez.
- Please leave a message...

386
00:20:56,972 --> 00:21:00,505
[Son]
Where is he, and why isn't he answering?

387
00:21:10,172 --> 00:21:11,405
You picked up right away.

388
00:21:11,405 --> 00:21:13,905
Were you expecting an important call?

389
00:21:13,905 --> 00:21:15,838
Expecting what?

390
00:21:15,838 --> 00:21:17,272
Why are you calling
this early in the morning?

391
00:21:17,272 --> 00:21:19,472
Would you like to grab some coffee?

392
00:21:24,838 --> 00:21:26,905
Is Du Jun doing alright?

393
00:21:26,905 --> 00:21:29,905
I saw the news and got worried.

394
00:21:29,905 --> 00:21:32,405
Du Jun would never do such things.

395
00:21:32,405 --> 00:21:34,405
It's probably all fake news anyway.

396
00:21:34,405 --> 00:21:37,072
Still, at the company, they're
treating it as a major incident.

397
00:21:37,072 --> 00:21:41,205
I mean, some of it does sound kind of true.

398
00:21:41,205 --> 00:21:42,938
Yeah?

399
00:21:42,938 --> 00:21:46,372
He hasn't told me anything about work lately.

400
00:21:46,372 --> 00:21:48,172
I didn't think much of it at first.

401
00:21:48,172 --> 00:21:50,505
But then I started to suspect

402
00:21:50,505 --> 00:21:52,438
the woman by his side.

403
00:21:54,205 --> 00:21:56,005
What woman?

404
00:21:56,005 --> 00:21:59,238
You didn't know he's seeing someone?

405
00:22:00,105 --> 00:22:01,538
Hold on.

406
00:22:01,538 --> 00:22:04,997
Are you saying there really is a woman?

407
00:22:04,997 --> 00:22:06,038
Oh.

408
00:22:06,038 --> 00:22:11,372
Come to think of it, I think he mentioned it
once at a blind date.

409
00:22:11,372 --> 00:22:14,149
Why? Do you know something?

410
00:22:14,149 --> 00:22:15,972
Oh.

411
00:22:15,972 --> 00:22:19,138
I'm not sure how to put this.

412
00:22:19,138 --> 00:22:24,572
At first when I learned she is
Se Hyeon's boss, it gave me a bad feeling.

413
00:22:24,572 --> 00:22:26,738
Turns out she's very ambitious.

414
00:22:26,738 --> 00:22:30,038
And seems to crave
climbing the social ladder.

415
00:22:30,038 --> 00:22:32,038
That much was understandable.

416
00:22:32,038 --> 00:22:33,805
But with Du Jun...

417
00:22:39,072 --> 00:22:41,638
Huh? What?

418
00:22:44,505 --> 00:22:50,138
Then that abortion story in the article...

419
00:22:51,038 --> 00:22:52,905
Oh my.

420
00:22:52,905 --> 00:22:54,638
Goodness.

421
00:22:55,772 --> 00:22:59,338
But surely he wouldn't do
something like that, right?

422
00:22:59,338 --> 00:23:01,872
Ugh, he's not even answering calls.

423
00:23:01,872 --> 00:23:04,938
Young people falling
for each other is one thing.

424
00:23:04,938 --> 00:23:07,272
But getting pregnant
right away? That's suspicious.

425
00:23:07,272 --> 00:23:11,105
To be blunt, are we even sure it's his child?

426
00:23:26,205 --> 00:23:28,872
These are all the solutions
we've come up with so far.

427
00:23:28,872 --> 00:23:30,638
Aren't they all essentially the same thing?

428
00:23:30,638 --> 00:23:32,105
We should release a rebuttal article
denying everything as groundless.

429
00:23:32,105 --> 00:23:34,438
At this point, that's
the most reliable solution.

430
00:23:34,438 --> 00:23:36,505
You're not thinking of
something else, are you?

431
00:23:36,505 --> 00:23:38,238
Like partially admitting to it?

432
00:23:38,238 --> 00:23:41,138
That won't work. Right now,
pretending we know nothing is

433
00:23:41,138 --> 00:23:42,305
more effective than telling the truth.

434
00:23:42,305 --> 00:23:43,338
You saw the stock price, didn't you?

435
00:23:43,338 --> 00:23:45,138
It dropped by eight percent in a single day.

436
00:23:45,138 --> 00:23:46,638
If you admit anything now,

437
00:23:46,638 --> 00:23:49,105
the company will completely collapse.

438
00:23:56,372 --> 00:23:58,105
President.

439
00:24:03,438 --> 00:24:05,138
Oh, Madam!

440
00:24:05,138 --> 00:24:06,338
What brings you here without even calling?

441
00:24:06,338 --> 00:24:11,338
I was just passing by
and thought I'd stop in.

442
00:24:11,338 --> 00:24:14,838
Is Du Jun very busy right now?

443
00:24:14,838 --> 00:24:17,238
The President is in a meeting.

444
00:24:17,238 --> 00:24:19,105
I'll tell him to wrap it up quickly and come.

445
00:24:19,105 --> 00:24:20,372
No, no.

446
00:24:20,372 --> 00:24:21,905
Why interrupt him during a meeting?

447
00:24:21,905 --> 00:24:23,672
I can wait a little.

448
00:24:23,672 --> 00:24:27,372
Then please have a seat.
I'll bring some tea right away.

449
00:24:28,405 --> 00:24:34,305
We have coffee, green tea, oolong tea,
brown rice tea, chamomile...

450
00:24:34,305 --> 00:24:35,738
Tea's fine.

451
00:24:35,738 --> 00:24:38,905
Just sit here for a moment.

452
00:24:38,905 --> 00:24:41,238
- Me?
- Yes.

453
00:24:41,238 --> 00:24:45,138
I want to ask you something.

454
00:24:46,772 --> 00:24:48,472
Okay.

455
00:24:49,172 --> 00:24:50,738
Well...

456
00:24:50,738 --> 00:24:54,805
I heard Du Jun is seeing a woman these days.

457
00:24:54,805 --> 00:24:57,405
Ah, that's...

458
00:24:57,405 --> 00:24:59,738
I'm just curious.

459
00:24:59,738 --> 00:25:02,533
You know who she is, right, Secretary Go?

460
00:25:02,533 --> 00:25:06,038
I heard she's Se Hyeon's
team leader or something.

461
00:25:06,038 --> 00:25:07,705
Is that true?

462
00:25:07,705 --> 00:25:09,672
Ah, well...

463
00:25:14,672 --> 00:25:16,838
Yes.

464
00:25:16,838 --> 00:25:21,638
I know Du Jun hates this kind of thing,

465
00:25:21,638 --> 00:25:25,829
but I'm just so curious, that's all.

466
00:25:25,829 --> 00:25:27,272
Well,

467
00:25:27,272 --> 00:25:29,572
with rumors

468
00:25:29,572 --> 00:25:33,572
of an abortion coming out, too...

469
00:25:36,372 --> 00:25:39,972
But you know better than anyone that
he isn't that kind of person.

470
00:25:39,972 --> 00:25:41,105
Right?

471
00:25:41,105 --> 00:25:42,705
Our Du Jun isn't that kind of boy, right?

472
00:25:42,705 --> 00:25:46,172
Besides, he's quite particular, isn't he?

473
00:25:46,172 --> 00:25:47,538
Yes, exactly.

474
00:25:47,538 --> 00:25:49,772
Whether he's working or at home,

475
00:25:49,772 --> 00:25:52,072
he's not very easygoing.

476
00:25:52,072 --> 00:25:54,072
He's not someone who dates lightly

477
00:25:54,072 --> 00:25:56,438
or breaks things off casually,
so please understand that much.

478
00:25:56,438 --> 00:26:00,293
The rumors circulating now
will be cleared up soon.

479
00:26:00,293 --> 00:26:03,772
If that's the case, that's a relief.

480
00:26:03,772 --> 00:26:07,072
You've known Du Jun a long time, so you know,

481
00:26:07,072 --> 00:26:10,438
but he won't even get married
because of his brother.

482
00:26:10,438 --> 00:26:13,472
So hearing that he suddenly has a girlfriend,

483
00:26:13,472 --> 00:26:16,272
or that there's a child involved,

484
00:26:16,272 --> 00:26:18,072
I...

485
00:26:18,072 --> 00:26:19,505
I...

486
00:26:19,505 --> 00:26:21,938
I was just...

487
00:26:23,038 --> 00:26:26,905
It was all so sudden and shocking.

488
00:26:28,338 --> 00:26:31,438
Of course, I completely understand.

489
00:26:33,638 --> 00:26:35,172
Please don't worry too much.

490
00:26:35,172 --> 00:26:38,072
The President has always lived honorably,

491
00:26:38,072 --> 00:26:39,905
and especially to take his brother's place,

492
00:26:39,905 --> 00:26:42,772
he's always given his best to every task.

493
00:26:42,772 --> 00:26:43,972
That's true.

494
00:26:43,972 --> 00:26:47,238
Whether as a child or now,

495
00:26:47,238 --> 00:26:50,005
when it came to Han Jun's work,

496
00:26:50,005 --> 00:26:52,738
he always stepped up to help.

497
00:26:52,738 --> 00:26:54,725
Du Jun

498
00:26:54,725 --> 00:26:58,405
adored his brother so much.

499
00:26:59,372 --> 00:27:02,338
I'm sure he still misses him terribly.

500
00:27:02,972 --> 00:27:07,072
Because of that guilt toward his brother,

501
00:27:07,072 --> 00:27:09,338
he never really lived a life of his own.

502
00:27:09,338 --> 00:27:14,772
So hearing rumors like this,
it just feels so unsettling.

503
00:27:14,772 --> 00:27:18,372
I miss him too.

504
00:27:18,372 --> 00:27:20,672
Just as much as Du Jun does.

505
00:27:21,872 --> 00:27:23,572
I also...

506
00:27:24,872 --> 00:27:27,538
I miss him too.

507
00:27:45,638 --> 00:27:46,772
I'm sorry.

508
00:27:46,772 --> 00:27:49,472
I'm being so emotional today.

509
00:27:57,338 --> 00:27:59,333
[Product introduction]
That's why I want to launch

510
00:27:59,333 --> 00:28:00,805
this high-proof beer this time.

511
00:28:00,805 --> 00:28:03,338
Among people who enjoy drinking,
it will definitely create a buzz.

512
00:28:03,338 --> 00:28:06,005
But I actually think
it might lack mass appeal.

513
00:28:06,005 --> 00:28:07,141
There's whiskey and baijiu

514
00:28:07,141 --> 00:28:09,138
- for high-proof drinks.
- Yeah.

515
00:28:09,138 --> 00:28:11,105
And people could just drink soju instead.

516
00:28:11,105 --> 00:28:13,705
Would people really want high-proof drinks
when they're drinking beer?

517
00:28:13,705 --> 00:28:14,972
Young lady.

518
00:28:14,972 --> 00:28:17,405
That's not how you
should be approaching this.

519
00:28:17,405 --> 00:28:20,338
What do you think, Manager Jang?

520
00:28:20,338 --> 00:28:21,938
Manager Jang?

521
00:28:21,938 --> 00:28:23,138
- Pardon?
- What?

522
00:28:23,138 --> 00:28:24,172
You've been acting strange lately.

523
00:28:24,172 --> 00:28:26,338
You've been zoning out at the office nonstop.

524
00:28:27,005 --> 00:28:31,272
I'm sorry. I'm not feeling well today.

525
00:28:31,272 --> 00:28:33,605
Well, there's nothing more to discuss anyway.

526
00:28:33,605 --> 00:28:34,638
Shall we end it here?

527
00:28:34,638 --> 00:28:37,138
Okay, let's talk again next time.

528
00:28:43,472 --> 00:28:44,772
Give it to me.

529
00:28:44,772 --> 00:28:46,938
I'm fine.

530
00:28:46,938 --> 00:28:49,738
I'll carry this for you
up to the office entrance.

531
00:28:49,738 --> 00:28:51,572
But are you really okay?

532
00:28:51,572 --> 00:28:53,541
You're not sick or anything?

533
00:28:53,541 --> 00:28:55,077
Oh, well.

534
00:28:55,077 --> 00:28:57,338
I think I'm just hungry.

535
00:28:57,338 --> 00:28:59,405
My blood sugar's crashing.

536
00:29:02,838 --> 00:29:04,572
Want to grab dinner together?

537
00:29:04,572 --> 00:29:08,372
There's a place that might
help you right now.

538
00:29:11,272 --> 00:29:15,138
We'll have one ricotta cheese salad,

539
00:29:15,138 --> 00:29:17,272
one mozzarella pomodoro,

540
00:29:17,272 --> 00:29:18,572
one aglio e olio as well,

541
00:29:18,572 --> 00:29:20,672
truffle fries,

542
00:29:20,672 --> 00:29:22,738
and two glasses of this, please.

543
00:29:22,738 --> 00:29:24,933
- Yes.
- Thank you.

544
00:29:25,784 --> 00:29:27,461
Oh.

545
00:29:32,338 --> 00:29:33,605
Jang Hui Won?

546
00:29:33,605 --> 00:29:35,438
Huh?

547
00:29:35,438 --> 00:29:36,705
Don't you remember this place?

548
00:29:36,705 --> 00:29:38,372
- Huh?
- After I joined the company,

549
00:29:38,372 --> 00:29:40,072
when I was first picked
as an outstanding employee,

550
00:29:40,072 --> 00:29:43,105
you brought me here to celebrate.

551
00:29:44,038 --> 00:29:46,572
Oh, right.

552
00:29:46,572 --> 00:29:48,472
I did.

553
00:29:49,105 --> 00:29:52,305
Then do you remember us
having non-alcoholic wine?

554
00:29:52,305 --> 00:29:54,705
Because I drove that day,

555
00:29:54,705 --> 00:29:56,338
we had no choice but to order
non-alcoholic drinks.

556
00:29:56,338 --> 00:29:58,272
You tasted it and then

557
00:29:58,272 --> 00:30:01,805
said the flavor and aroma were incredible,
and even gave it a standing ovation.

558
00:30:01,805 --> 00:30:03,838
A standing ovation? Me?

559
00:30:03,838 --> 00:30:08,138
Well, that's what it felt like.

560
00:30:08,138 --> 00:30:10,238
You're really...

561
00:30:11,105 --> 00:30:12,505
I ordered a glass each for us again today.

562
00:30:12,505 --> 00:30:15,305
Thought you could try it again

563
00:30:15,305 --> 00:30:18,405
and use it as a reference
for your non-alcoholic beer.

564
00:30:19,438 --> 00:30:23,172
Hey, where else would you
find a friend like this?

565
00:30:40,038 --> 00:30:43,838
You're not someone who gets full this easily.

566
00:30:45,472 --> 00:30:48,438
I guess my digestion isn't great today.

567
00:30:49,272 --> 00:30:51,905
Why? Because of the President?

568
00:30:52,938 --> 00:30:57,072
You kept looking at your phone
ever since the meeting earlier.

569
00:30:57,072 --> 00:31:02,105
He's probably frantically
busy looking for alternatives,

570
00:31:02,105 --> 00:31:05,538
but I feel like I'm no help at all.

571
00:31:05,538 --> 00:31:07,525
Should you

572
00:31:07,525 --> 00:31:10,072
really stay by his side like this?

573
00:31:10,772 --> 00:31:15,138
It's exhausting even now, and there's
no guarantee this won't happen again.

574
00:31:17,538 --> 00:31:20,405
If it were me, I wouldn't
have let this happen.

575
00:31:20,405 --> 00:31:24,238
I would've answered every call,
never made you wait.

576
00:31:24,238 --> 00:31:27,138
No matter what, I would've
stayed by your side.

577
00:31:27,138 --> 00:31:29,472
I know. I get it too.

578
00:31:29,472 --> 00:31:31,672
He has a lot of responsibilities
to deal with.

579
00:31:31,672 --> 00:31:34,538
But still,

580
00:31:34,538 --> 00:31:36,805
I hate seeing you struggle.

581
00:31:42,205 --> 00:31:43,872
This is my choice too.

582
00:31:43,872 --> 00:31:46,205
I knew it wouldn't be easy when I started,

583
00:31:46,205 --> 00:31:49,238
so rather than regretting that choice,

584
00:31:49,238 --> 00:31:53,405
I want to do my best in whatever I can do.

585
00:31:53,405 --> 00:31:55,438
Thanks for worrying about me.

586
00:31:55,438 --> 00:31:57,172
I'll get through this.

587
00:31:57,172 --> 00:31:59,872
You know I'm strong in a crisis.

588
00:32:13,605 --> 00:32:15,638
Should you really stay by his side like this?

589
00:32:15,638 --> 00:32:16,872
It's exhausting even now,

590
00:32:16,872 --> 00:32:18,872
and there's no guarantee
this won't happen again.

591
00:32:18,872 --> 00:32:21,038
I hate seeing you struggle.

592
00:32:35,333 --> 00:32:36,405
Well.

593
00:32:36,405 --> 00:32:40,405
I'm sorry. If I'd known you were coming,
I would've at least bought some fruit.

594
00:32:40,405 --> 00:32:42,805
You must really love beer.

595
00:32:42,805 --> 00:32:45,029
Your whole house shows it.

596
00:32:45,029 --> 00:32:49,038
Oh, when I get fixated on something,
I tend to obsess over it.

597
00:32:49,038 --> 00:32:52,421
Now I finally understand why you cried over
not being able to drink at the restaurant.

598
00:32:52,421 --> 00:32:53,872
Oh.

599
00:32:53,872 --> 00:32:56,672
Please forget about that.

600
00:32:58,305 --> 00:33:00,405
You're so pure, Hui Won.

601
00:33:00,405 --> 00:33:02,905
That's why I like you so much.

602
00:33:02,905 --> 00:33:06,238
So I came in person for this final warning.

603
00:33:06,238 --> 00:33:10,238
- Pardon?
- I'm the one who leaked the article.

604
00:33:10,238 --> 00:33:14,405
My goal is to bring down Du Jun.

605
00:33:14,405 --> 00:33:17,072
But that is just between him and me.

606
00:33:17,072 --> 00:33:20,672
Before anyone else gets hurt,
break up with him.

607
00:33:20,672 --> 00:33:22,605
That's why I came to say this.

608
00:33:39,005 --> 00:33:41,672
I bear you no ill will.

609
00:33:41,672 --> 00:33:44,238
That's why I'm telling you kindly.

610
00:33:44,238 --> 00:33:46,105
Run away.

611
00:33:46,738 --> 00:33:48,172
If you don't,

612
00:33:48,172 --> 00:33:50,305
I'll have no choice but to play my next card.

613
00:33:50,305 --> 00:33:54,405
And then he might not be able to recover.

614
00:33:54,405 --> 00:33:56,972
Think carefully

615
00:33:56,972 --> 00:34:00,005
about what truly protects him.

616
00:34:00,005 --> 00:34:03,105
Why are you going this far? You're family.

617
00:34:03,105 --> 00:34:05,172
Well,

618
00:34:05,172 --> 00:34:07,838
I doubt you'd understand even if I told you.

619
00:34:07,838 --> 00:34:09,938
No, I don't understand.

620
00:34:09,938 --> 00:34:11,872
And I don't understand
why you're telling me all this.

621
00:34:11,872 --> 00:34:13,372
Because you're pure, Hui Won.

622
00:34:13,372 --> 00:34:16,972
Kind, harmless,

623
00:34:19,472 --> 00:34:21,905
and pitiful to look at,
so I don't want to hurt you either.

624
00:34:21,905 --> 00:34:24,238
So don't waste your energy.

625
00:34:24,238 --> 00:34:27,272
There's nothing you'll be able to do

626
00:34:27,272 --> 00:34:29,205
from now on.

627
00:34:49,705 --> 00:34:52,138
Here's your bill.

628
00:34:52,138 --> 00:34:53,905
Thank you.

629
00:35:12,038 --> 00:35:14,738
You left your wallet, but why
haven't you contacted me?

630
00:35:14,738 --> 00:35:17,405
Let's meet tomorrow.
I'll give it back to you.

631
00:35:19,305 --> 00:35:21,405
I explained it clearly, so don't worry.

632
00:35:21,405 --> 00:35:24,572
Couldn't we just expose that woman first?

633
00:35:24,572 --> 00:35:27,338
If Du Jun releases a denial article first...

634
00:35:27,338 --> 00:35:29,072
Struggling won't change anything.

635
00:35:29,072 --> 00:35:33,072
Something much more interesting
will happen tomorrow, so look forward to it.

636
00:35:38,172 --> 00:35:43,472
- Step down! Step down!
- Hello.

637
00:35:43,472 --> 00:35:44,505
[Female employees are not Kang Du Jun's toys]
Step down!

638
00:35:44,505 --> 00:35:47,705
A CEO who uses women as tools must step down!

639
00:35:47,705 --> 00:35:49,438
Step down! Step down!

640
00:35:49,438 --> 00:35:51,238
[Taehan Liquor remains silent]
Kang Du Jun, who tramples the weak

641
00:35:51,238 --> 00:35:52,572
[Dismiss Kang Du Jun for deceiving consumers]
with power, must apologize!

642
00:35:52,572 --> 00:35:54,438
Apologize! Apologize!

643
00:35:54,438 --> 00:35:57,838
Kang Du Jun, resign from Taehan Liquor!

644
00:35:57,838 --> 00:35:59,972
[Resign, consumer-deceiving, abusive CEO]
Resign! Resign!

645
00:35:59,972 --> 00:36:02,205
Hey, Cha Min Uk.

646
00:36:02,205 --> 00:36:03,938
What? Did you take a day off because of me?

647
00:36:03,938 --> 00:36:06,938
I've got a field trip this afternoon,
so I have a bit of time this morning.

648
00:36:06,938 --> 00:36:08,872
Then you have to head back soon.

649
00:36:08,872 --> 00:36:11,738
Didn't you call me to give me my wallet?

650
00:36:11,738 --> 00:36:14,172
Okay, well, if I push hard,
I should be able to make it.

651
00:36:14,172 --> 00:36:15,938
Huh? Make what?

652
00:36:15,938 --> 00:36:18,238
Hey, let's go. Hurry up,
we don't have time. Let's go.

653
00:36:18,238 --> 00:36:20,338
Hey, where are we going?

654
00:36:20,338 --> 00:36:22,505
Ah, I'm full.

655
00:36:24,638 --> 00:36:26,338
Since we're done eating,

656
00:36:26,338 --> 00:36:28,805
can you give me my wallet now?

657
00:36:28,805 --> 00:36:29,938
Do you want to have some coffee?

658
00:36:29,938 --> 00:36:31,505
No, I'm craving something sweet.

659
00:36:31,505 --> 00:36:33,238
Something sweet?

660
00:36:33,972 --> 00:36:36,838
Wow, that looks good.

661
00:36:36,838 --> 00:36:38,805
Hey, what do you want?

662
00:36:38,805 --> 00:36:40,738
- I'll pay for this.
- Jeez.

663
00:36:40,738 --> 00:36:42,838
You don't even have your wallet,
and you're acting cocky.

664
00:36:42,838 --> 00:36:44,138
Because I'm paying for everything today.

665
00:36:44,138 --> 00:36:45,438
You want this?

666
00:36:45,438 --> 00:36:48,072
Should I get a croissant too?

667
00:36:49,538 --> 00:36:51,438
I feel like I'm going to burst.

668
00:36:51,438 --> 00:36:54,438
But did you even eat anything?

669
00:36:54,438 --> 00:36:56,372
I ate a lot too.

670
00:36:56,372 --> 00:36:59,538
Now stop beating around
the bush and give me my wallet.

671
00:36:59,538 --> 00:37:01,172
Give it, my wallet, my wallet.

672
00:37:01,172 --> 00:37:03,072
Alright, I'll give it back. That darn wallet.

673
00:37:03,072 --> 00:37:05,138
I'll take you to the office.

674
00:37:05,872 --> 00:37:07,005
You don't have to.

675
00:37:07,005 --> 00:37:08,105
Just give it to me here.

676
00:37:08,105 --> 00:37:11,272
Ah, I'm full, let's walk a bit.
The weather is nice.

677
00:37:11,272 --> 00:37:12,572
The weather is so nice, right?

678
00:37:12,572 --> 00:37:14,572
Wow, unbelievable.

679
00:37:14,572 --> 00:37:16,005
Did you see it?

680
00:37:16,005 --> 00:37:18,138
The protesters are everywhere.

681
00:37:18,138 --> 00:37:19,438
I just went to buy a coffee

682
00:37:19,438 --> 00:37:20,645
and they'd already blocked the entrance.

683
00:37:20,645 --> 00:37:21,705
I almost couldn't get in.

684
00:37:21,705 --> 00:37:23,605
It seems like the number of
reporters is increasing.

685
00:37:23,605 --> 00:37:25,205
Will our company be in the news?

686
00:37:25,205 --> 00:37:26,838
What's going to happen
to our company's image?

687
00:37:26,838 --> 00:37:30,905
My junior was raving about wanting
to join our company not long ago.

688
00:37:30,905 --> 00:37:32,905
But she's gone completely quiet about it now.

689
00:37:32,905 --> 00:37:36,305
She said our company is too chaotic
and she's thinking of going to a competitor.

690
00:37:36,305 --> 00:37:39,938
No wonder, Office Talk is full of posts
criticizing the company and the President.

691
00:37:39,938 --> 00:37:41,672
It might not even be true.

692
00:37:41,672 --> 00:37:44,872
Because they're still just rumors.

693
00:37:45,638 --> 00:37:49,538
Se Hyeon, you're still young,
so you don't know how scary the world can be.

694
00:37:49,538 --> 00:37:50,938
There's no smoke without fire.

695
00:37:50,938 --> 00:37:54,872
If there were no basis, would there be
this many news articles and protesters?

696
00:37:54,872 --> 00:37:56,838
There must be something
for it to be like this.

697
00:37:56,838 --> 00:38:00,938
But in fact, nothing's been
clearly proven yet, right?

698
00:38:01,605 --> 00:38:02,838
I'm going to stay neutral for now.

699
00:38:02,838 --> 00:38:05,738
Our president doesn't
seem like the type to do that.

700
00:38:05,738 --> 00:38:07,705
What? Why are you suddenly
neutral by yourself?

701
00:38:07,705 --> 00:38:09,772
Then I'll wait and see for now.

702
00:38:09,772 --> 00:38:10,905
Right.

703
00:38:10,905 --> 00:38:14,725
Manager Jang, about that ale beer, I need
the projected convenience store sales file...

704
00:38:14,725 --> 00:38:15,938
Where did she go?

705
00:38:15,938 --> 00:38:19,205
She said she was taking emergency leave
today and contacted you this morning.

706
00:38:19,205 --> 00:38:20,205
Huh? Didn't you hear?

707
00:38:20,205 --> 00:38:21,438
Oh, right.

708
00:38:21,438 --> 00:38:24,738
Because of those protesters,
I've been completely frazzled since morning.

709
00:38:24,738 --> 00:38:26,638
Okay, get back to work.

710
00:38:28,538 --> 00:38:30,005
But why did she take the day off?

711
00:38:30,005 --> 00:38:32,038
I don't know either.

712
00:38:32,038 --> 00:38:33,105
Maybe she went on a trip?

713
00:38:33,105 --> 00:38:34,438
Must be nice.

714
00:38:34,438 --> 00:38:37,905
- I want to go on a trip too.
- Hey, but there are too many protesters.

715
00:38:37,905 --> 00:38:40,005
Step down! Step down!

716
00:38:40,005 --> 00:38:43,838
A CEO who uses women as tools must step down!

717
00:38:43,838 --> 00:38:45,872
Step down! Step down!

718
00:38:45,872 --> 00:38:48,272
Kang Du Jun, who tramples the weak
with power, must apologize!

719
00:38:48,272 --> 00:38:50,338
- What? They're even holding a protest?
- Apologize! Apologize!

720
00:38:50,338 --> 00:38:51,705
This is no joke.

721
00:38:51,705 --> 00:38:53,372
So just give it back and go.

722
00:38:53,372 --> 00:38:55,172
- There's no good in us being here.
- Kang Du Jun, resign from Taehan Liquor!

723
00:38:55,172 --> 00:38:59,072
- Oh, are you worried about me now?
- Resign! Resign!

724
00:38:59,072 --> 00:39:02,005
- There you go again.
- Okay, I'll give it to you.

725
00:39:02,005 --> 00:39:05,038
- I'll go, here.
- Kang Du Jun must apologize!

726
00:39:05,038 --> 00:39:06,505
Apologize! Apologize!

727
00:39:06,505 --> 00:39:07,605
I know

728
00:39:07,605 --> 00:39:10,438
- you like Hui Won.
- Kang Du Jun must step down!

729
00:39:10,438 --> 00:39:13,638
I know this isn't the time
for you to be messing around.

730
00:39:13,638 --> 00:39:15,272
Because you must be having a headache now.

731
00:39:15,272 --> 00:39:17,238
[Kang Du Jun out!]
The company is in chaos right now.

732
00:39:17,238 --> 00:39:18,972
You're worried about Hui Won.

733
00:39:18,972 --> 00:39:21,705
But Hui Won is only
worried about Kang Du Jun.

734
00:39:21,705 --> 00:39:25,172
For me, Hui Won is one thing,
but I'm worried about you too.

735
00:39:25,172 --> 00:39:29,205
That's why I did this. If I didn't do this,
would you even hang out with me?

736
00:39:29,838 --> 00:39:32,605
Here, take it. For real.

737
00:39:34,438 --> 00:39:36,504
I'm leaving.

738
00:39:58,205 --> 00:39:59,772
Wow.

739
00:39:59,772 --> 00:40:02,272
As expected, you're unstoppable.

740
00:40:02,272 --> 00:40:03,438
Seriously.

741
00:40:03,438 --> 00:40:07,205
You knew all along that they couldn't
even publish anything

742
00:40:07,205 --> 00:40:08,538
to refute the false accusation.

743
00:40:08,538 --> 00:40:10,238
That awkward sense of responsibility,

744
00:40:10,238 --> 00:40:11,772
that's exactly him.

745
00:40:11,772 --> 00:40:12,972
Wow.

746
00:40:12,972 --> 00:40:17,405
His foolishness in protecting something small
while losing something bigger

747
00:40:17,405 --> 00:40:19,372
always holds him back.

748
00:40:19,372 --> 00:40:22,605
Good thing we're on the same side.

749
00:40:22,605 --> 00:40:28,772
When it comes to money and power,
family means nothing, it's brutal.

750
00:40:28,772 --> 00:40:31,038
You're the one who's truly wise.

751
00:40:31,038 --> 00:40:32,069
Just wait and see.

752
00:40:32,069 --> 00:40:33,905
I'll shake him down mentally so much

753
00:40:33,905 --> 00:40:36,672
he'll come down on his own.

754
00:40:38,005 --> 00:40:43,405
By the way, my brother
isn't the kind to stay still.

755
00:40:43,405 --> 00:40:45,701
Especially when

756
00:40:45,701 --> 00:40:47,338
it involves his son.

757
00:40:47,338 --> 00:40:48,705
Then it'll be easy.

758
00:40:48,705 --> 00:40:51,572
Because his weaknesses are extremely obvious.

759
00:40:59,705 --> 00:41:00,972
Why are you in such a hurry?

760
00:41:00,972 --> 00:41:02,072
You're even against an autopsy.

761
00:41:02,072 --> 00:41:03,572
Without a proper investigation,

762
00:41:03,572 --> 00:41:05,705
why are you rushing to cover everything up?

763
00:41:05,705 --> 00:41:08,305
Han Jun is your son too.

764
00:41:08,938 --> 00:41:10,205
The living need to live.

765
00:41:10,205 --> 00:41:11,905
Father!

766
00:41:12,605 --> 00:41:14,172
I know what you're thinking.

767
00:41:14,172 --> 00:41:16,205
But Du Jun isn't that kind of person.

768
00:41:16,205 --> 00:41:18,438
That's just your perspective, Father.

769
00:41:19,072 --> 00:41:20,772
My world has collapsed.

770
00:41:20,772 --> 00:41:22,805
Everything I ever dreamed of,

771
00:41:22,805 --> 00:41:24,872
the future we were supposed to share,

772
00:41:24,872 --> 00:41:27,905
and even Se Hyeon's father.

773
00:41:27,905 --> 00:41:30,838
Our entire family has fallen apart.

774
00:41:51,172 --> 00:41:54,938
A CEO who uses women as tools must step down!

775
00:41:54,938 --> 00:41:56,972
Step down! Step down!

776
00:41:56,972 --> 00:42:00,872
A CEO who tramples the weak
with power, must apologize.

777
00:42:00,872 --> 00:42:02,705
Apologize! Apologize!

778
00:42:02,705 --> 00:42:04,472
When did the protesters gather?

779
00:42:04,472 --> 00:42:06,538
Kang Du Jun, resign from Taehan Liquor!

780
00:42:06,538 --> 00:42:08,872
- Wait, I'll check.
- Resign! Resign!

781
00:42:08,872 --> 00:42:11,805
Dismiss Kang Du Jun for deceiving consumers!

782
00:42:11,805 --> 00:42:13,472
Dismiss him! Dismiss him!

783
00:42:13,472 --> 00:42:14,538
It's Kang Du Jun.

784
00:42:14,538 --> 00:42:16,838
The abusive President Kang Du Jun...

785
00:42:16,838 --> 00:42:18,372
- Mr. Kang Du Jun!
- Hey!

786
00:42:18,372 --> 00:42:20,572
- Mr. Kang Du Jun!
- Si Hyeong, get in quickly.

787
00:42:20,572 --> 00:42:25,005
- Mr. Kang Du Jun!
- Mr. Kang Du Jun!

788
00:42:25,005 --> 00:42:27,109
Mr. Kang Du Jun!

789
00:42:27,109 --> 00:42:29,093
Mr. Kang Du Jun!

790
00:42:29,093 --> 00:42:31,608
Please say something!

791
00:42:58,072 --> 00:43:02,105
Why do they have to chase us this far?

792
00:43:02,105 --> 00:43:03,805
Calm down a bit.

793
00:43:09,669 --> 00:43:11,237
Watch out!

794
00:43:41,572 --> 00:43:42,572
Get in.

795
00:43:42,572 --> 00:43:44,872
Huh? Hui Won?

796
00:43:50,472 --> 00:43:51,505
Si Hyeong, please handle them.

797
00:43:51,505 --> 00:43:52,805
Okay, Hui Won, go!

798
00:43:52,805 --> 00:43:54,505
- Yes.
- Hurry.

799
00:44:09,472 --> 00:44:11,005
But how did you know to come here?

800
00:44:11,005 --> 00:44:13,638
Protesters were everywhere on my way to work.

801
00:44:13,638 --> 00:44:16,238
I figured something big must be happening.

802
00:44:16,238 --> 00:44:17,972
What about work?

803
00:44:17,972 --> 00:44:20,438
Is work important right now?

804
00:44:21,572 --> 00:44:24,772
So you know how to drive all along?

805
00:44:24,772 --> 00:44:28,972
I just don't have a car,
but it's not that I can't drive.

806
00:44:49,772 --> 00:44:52,905
Wow, this feels refreshing.

807
00:44:53,838 --> 00:44:56,805
Aren't you overdoing it for my sake?

808
00:44:57,438 --> 00:44:59,838
It's good.

809
00:44:59,838 --> 00:45:04,238
Lately, nothing seems to go my way,

810
00:45:04,238 --> 00:45:08,938
and I've been frustrated
that I can't do anything.

811
00:45:08,938 --> 00:45:13,205
Now I feel as if a huge weight
has been lifted.

812
00:45:16,338 --> 00:45:18,272
Don't apologize.

813
00:45:18,272 --> 00:45:20,838
Because it wasn't your fault.

814
00:45:22,438 --> 00:45:24,172
Thank you.

815
00:45:28,672 --> 00:45:30,205
Aren't you hungry?

816
00:45:30,205 --> 00:45:32,772
I skipped work for the first time
in my life today.

817
00:45:32,772 --> 00:45:34,338
- Let's go have some fun.
- Huh?

818
00:45:34,338 --> 00:45:36,838
Quickly, quickly. Let's go quickly.

819
00:45:38,705 --> 00:45:40,405
How is it?

820
00:45:41,105 --> 00:45:42,872
It's fascinating.

821
00:45:43,772 --> 00:45:45,138
Is this your first time at a market?

822
00:45:45,138 --> 00:45:47,538
- Yes.
- How rustic.

823
00:45:47,538 --> 00:45:48,705
Is it really that rustic?

824
00:45:48,705 --> 00:45:50,205
Of course.

825
00:45:50,205 --> 00:45:51,572
Look over there.

826
00:45:51,572 --> 00:45:53,272
Over there.

827
00:45:55,938 --> 00:45:56,938
How do I look?

828
00:45:56,938 --> 00:45:58,205
- It suits you well.
- Yeah?

829
00:45:58,205 --> 00:46:00,072
Then you should try this on, President.

830
00:46:00,072 --> 00:46:01,772
Me?

831
00:46:05,038 --> 00:46:06,072
How do I look?

832
00:46:06,072 --> 00:46:07,805
It looks great.

833
00:46:22,405 --> 00:46:23,838
Pupa!

834
00:46:23,838 --> 00:46:24,838
I'm fine.

835
00:46:24,838 --> 00:46:26,672
It actually tastes amazing,
despite how it looks.

836
00:46:26,672 --> 00:46:28,005
It looks terrifying.

837
00:46:28,005 --> 00:46:29,538
Just try it once.

838
00:46:29,538 --> 00:46:30,672
- No.
- Just once.

839
00:46:30,672 --> 00:46:32,005
- Please.
- Just once.

840
00:46:32,005 --> 00:46:34,661
- Open it.
- I really can't eat this.

841
00:46:37,238 --> 00:46:38,238
How is it?

842
00:46:38,238 --> 00:46:40,105
I'm telling you, it's good!

843
00:46:40,105 --> 00:46:41,972
See? I was right.

844
00:46:41,972 --> 00:46:43,672
It's the perfect time for it.

845
00:46:43,672 --> 00:46:45,005
You two look so good together.

846
00:46:45,005 --> 00:46:47,372
Enjoy yourselves while you're young.

847
00:46:52,938 --> 00:46:54,053
[Sailfin sandfish and sand eels]

848
00:46:58,572 --> 00:47:01,005
Wow, the fruit looks delicious.

849
00:47:01,005 --> 00:47:02,838
Do you want some fruit?

850
00:47:03,838 --> 00:47:05,905
It's hard to choose.

851
00:47:15,621 --> 00:47:16,705
Are you newlyweds?

852
00:47:16,705 --> 00:47:18,472
Pardon?

853
00:47:18,472 --> 00:47:20,905
You just look so fresh and lovely together.

854
00:47:20,905 --> 00:47:23,205
Among all the people
who came to our market this year,

855
00:47:23,205 --> 00:47:26,405
you two are the prettiest
and the most handsome.

856
00:47:26,405 --> 00:47:27,438
Thank you.

857
00:47:27,438 --> 00:47:30,205
Jeez, I wonder when I'll ever get married.

858
00:47:30,205 --> 00:47:32,138
The only thing that makes eye contact with me

859
00:47:32,138 --> 00:47:36,138
is the flounder at that fish stall.

860
00:47:36,138 --> 00:47:39,972
Here, try this. It's tasty.

861
00:47:39,972 --> 00:47:42,072
Thank you.

862
00:47:42,072 --> 00:47:44,272
It reminds me of you two,

863
00:47:44,272 --> 00:47:46,172
so fresh and lively.

864
00:47:47,138 --> 00:47:49,305
- Come again.
- Yes.

865
00:47:50,572 --> 00:47:52,305
Let's go.

866
00:48:39,905 --> 00:48:41,605
Thank you.

867
00:48:45,772 --> 00:48:46,838
What?

868
00:48:46,838 --> 00:48:49,005
It's a shame.

869
00:48:49,705 --> 00:48:54,238
I felt like, 'My free time
is slipping away like this.'

870
00:48:56,472 --> 00:49:02,305
I never even got to enjoy things like this.
What was all that running for?

871
00:49:02,305 --> 00:49:05,505
The first time is the hardest,
but it'll get easier after the second time.

872
00:49:05,505 --> 00:49:07,705
Let's skip work together
more often from now on.

873
00:49:07,705 --> 00:49:08,805
Jeez.

874
00:49:08,805 --> 00:49:13,138
Is it appropriate for the President
to tell employees to skip work?

875
00:49:23,472 --> 00:49:24,738
Well,

876
00:49:24,738 --> 00:49:30,338
remember the story you
told me about your brother?

877
00:49:31,605 --> 00:49:33,372
Yes.

878
00:49:33,372 --> 00:49:35,238
How is your relationship
with your sister-in-law?

879
00:49:35,238 --> 00:49:37,338
Why are you asking that all of a sudden?

880
00:49:37,338 --> 00:49:38,738
Just wondering.

881
00:49:38,738 --> 00:49:40,905
When the three of us met last time,

882
00:49:40,905 --> 00:49:43,738
it seemed like there was
some tension between you two.

883
00:49:46,272 --> 00:49:48,105
It can't be good.

884
00:49:48,105 --> 00:49:50,272
Not after something like that.

885
00:49:51,138 --> 00:49:52,838
I see.

886
00:50:00,572 --> 00:50:03,338
President, there's something
I need to tell you.

887
00:50:05,572 --> 00:50:07,338
What if we just pretend

888
00:50:08,272 --> 00:50:10,972
we don't know each other?

889
00:50:11,738 --> 00:50:13,338
What?

890
00:50:13,338 --> 00:50:16,638
I don't have the confidence
to handle this kind of life,

891
00:50:16,638 --> 00:50:18,938
and I don't want Yeol Mu

892
00:50:18,938 --> 00:50:22,105
to get criticized when I'm exposed.

893
00:50:22,105 --> 00:50:24,338
So let's just hide everything.

894
00:50:24,338 --> 00:50:27,905
Deny it. Say it's groundless.

895
00:50:29,205 --> 00:50:30,505
What is it all of a sudden?

896
00:50:30,505 --> 00:50:33,672
Did you hear something somewhere?

897
00:50:33,672 --> 00:50:35,805
I'm scared.

898
00:50:35,805 --> 00:50:40,138
Last time, I tried to step up
and reveal everything,

899
00:50:40,138 --> 00:50:42,805
but I immediately regretted it.

900
00:50:43,605 --> 00:50:45,338
Just like you said,

901
00:50:45,338 --> 00:50:50,572
I don't like having all my effort dismissed
as some 'favor' from you.

902
00:50:50,572 --> 00:50:52,261
I just

903
00:50:52,261 --> 00:50:55,305
hate being the subject of gossip.

904
00:51:00,838 --> 00:51:03,005
So, let's just

905
00:51:06,338 --> 00:51:09,038
keep some distance.

906
00:51:09,038 --> 00:51:11,138
Are you serious?

907
00:51:26,338 --> 00:51:27,972
If you want me to explain instead, I will.

908
00:51:27,972 --> 00:51:29,705
If you want me to reveal
everything, I'll do it.

909
00:51:29,705 --> 00:51:33,538
I'll do anything to clear his name.

910
00:51:33,538 --> 00:51:38,705
So please, don't tell me
to break up with him.

911
00:51:38,705 --> 00:51:42,305
I know it's absurd
after causing all this trouble.

912
00:51:42,305 --> 00:51:43,672
That's why

913
00:51:43,672 --> 00:51:46,338
I've been thinking carefully

914
00:51:46,338 --> 00:51:48,505
and speaking with difficulty.

915
00:51:50,538 --> 00:51:55,672
Now I understand why Du Jun
is trying so hard to protect you.

916
00:51:55,672 --> 00:51:56,672
Pardon?

917
00:51:56,672 --> 00:51:57,972
You're going to do anything?

918
00:51:57,972 --> 00:52:00,905
Then, Hui Won, you have to help me.

919
00:52:00,905 --> 00:52:03,672
Du Jun might not listen to me,

920
00:52:03,672 --> 00:52:06,572
but he'll probably listen to you.

921
00:52:12,538 --> 00:52:16,405
Is that really what you want?

922
00:52:16,405 --> 00:52:18,438
Look me in the eye and tell me.

923
00:52:18,438 --> 00:52:21,905
Are you saying we should deny both you

924
00:52:21,905 --> 00:52:24,372
and our Yeol Mu in front of everyone?

925
00:52:24,372 --> 00:52:26,438
- Wouldn't that hurt your feelings?
- Why would it hurt my feelings?

926
00:52:26,438 --> 00:52:28,872
It's okay to tell a little lie sometimes.

927
00:52:28,872 --> 00:52:31,805
Hiding it doesn't mean it disappears.
Why does it matter?

928
00:52:31,805 --> 00:52:33,372
If anyone asks,

929
00:52:33,372 --> 00:52:35,472
I can hide you, President,
as many times as needed.

930
00:52:35,472 --> 00:52:36,972
I have to survive first,

931
00:52:36,972 --> 00:52:38,838
right?

932
00:52:43,505 --> 00:52:45,572
Hui Won.

933
00:52:45,572 --> 00:52:47,272
Jang Hui Won.

934
00:52:49,138 --> 00:52:51,172
Are you just going to leave like this?

935
00:52:55,505 --> 00:52:56,938
I called him.

936
00:52:56,938 --> 00:52:59,105
President, please take Secretary Go's car.

937
00:52:59,105 --> 00:53:01,405
Let's part ways here.

938
00:53:28,472 --> 00:53:29,538
What happened?

939
00:53:29,538 --> 00:53:31,172
Wasn't she coming to save you?

940
00:53:31,172 --> 00:53:34,972
She asked me to pretend not to know,
said it's okay to deny it.

941
00:53:34,972 --> 00:53:36,709
But for some reason,

942
00:53:36,709 --> 00:53:38,705
it didn't feel like she meant it.

943
00:53:38,705 --> 00:53:40,072
You know

944
00:53:40,072 --> 00:53:41,805
how careful Hui Won is.

945
00:53:41,805 --> 00:53:43,705
The fact that such a person said that means

946
00:53:43,705 --> 00:53:45,538
she must be

947
00:53:45,538 --> 00:53:48,172
worried about you that much.

948
00:53:51,672 --> 00:53:53,338
Du Jun.

949
00:53:53,338 --> 00:53:55,838
There must be a reason
everyone is saying that.

950
00:53:55,838 --> 00:53:58,105
It's just for now.

951
00:53:58,105 --> 00:54:04,072
Take care of the urgent matters first.
There's no rush to reveal the truth.

952
00:54:04,072 --> 00:54:05,872
I'll help you.

953
00:54:19,172 --> 00:54:21,138
Did I do the right thing?

954
00:54:23,738 --> 00:54:27,205
But this is the way to protect him.

955
00:54:29,605 --> 00:54:31,305
You did well.

956
00:54:32,138 --> 00:54:34,505
It was the best you could do.

957
00:55:29,573 --> 00:55:32,538
Please leave a message after the beep...

958
00:56:07,621 --> 00:56:08,938
Manager Jang took a day off today.

959
00:56:08,938 --> 00:56:11,605
- Day off?
- Haven't you contacted her?

960
00:56:14,805 --> 00:56:16,372
I know you're having a hard time, Uncle.

961
00:56:16,372 --> 00:56:18,705
But Manager Jang has been struggling too.

962
00:56:18,705 --> 00:56:22,072
Lately, people in the office
have all been suspecting her.

963
00:56:22,072 --> 00:56:25,572
You probably know best
how things should be done,

964
00:56:25,572 --> 00:56:27,605
but try to understand her feelings too.

965
00:56:27,605 --> 00:56:29,405
There's two of them now.

966
00:57:36,172 --> 00:57:38,338
Gather the reporters tomorrow.

967
00:57:38,338 --> 00:57:40,538
I'm going to hold a press conference.

968
00:57:50,505 --> 00:57:51,638
Big news! Big news!

969
00:57:51,638 --> 00:57:53,805
They're holding
a press conference at 3 PM today.

970
00:57:53,805 --> 00:57:55,138
He's going to explain everything?

971
00:57:55,138 --> 00:57:57,272
So, is he going to say
who the woman in the rumor is?

972
00:57:57,272 --> 00:57:59,005
Yes.

973
00:58:02,840 --> 00:58:04,421
I'm dying to know.

974
00:58:08,505 --> 00:58:09,838
A press conference?

975
00:58:09,838 --> 00:58:11,272
Not just a rebuttal article?

976
00:58:11,272 --> 00:58:12,472
Don't worry too much.

977
00:58:12,472 --> 00:58:14,105
Nothing serious will happen.

978
00:58:14,105 --> 00:58:16,705
Okay, got it. Thanks.

979
00:58:28,538 --> 00:58:31,805
[Press conference on Taehan Liquor CEO
Kang Du Jun's scandal]

980
00:58:31,805 --> 00:58:34,705
Unexpected. He's choosing a head-on approach.

981
00:58:34,705 --> 00:58:38,705
Since the explanation was delayed,
it seems he wants to apologize properly.

982
00:58:44,088 --> 00:58:45,541
[Official apology statement]

983
00:59:06,638 --> 00:59:08,572
First,

984
00:59:08,572 --> 00:59:11,005
regarding the reports about me
over the past few days,

985
00:59:11,005 --> 00:59:12,933
[Kang Du Jun issues urgent statement]
I apologize

986
00:59:12,933 --> 00:59:14,772
[regarding personal life controversy]
for causing concern.

987
00:59:16,921 --> 00:59:19,905
[Taehan Liquor President Kang Du Jun
issues urgent statement]

988
00:59:19,905 --> 00:59:21,038
Sir, please hurry.

989
00:59:21,038 --> 00:59:22,138
Please go quickly.

990
00:59:22,138 --> 00:59:23,305
Yes, understood.

991
00:59:23,305 --> 00:59:25,938
But let me make this clear.

992
00:59:25,938 --> 00:59:27,738
The report

993
00:59:30,605 --> 00:59:32,738
and its contents

994
00:59:33,805 --> 00:59:37,253
are completely false.

995
00:59:37,253 --> 00:59:40,672
- What?
- All false?

996
00:59:40,672 --> 00:59:45,205
At least, based on the articles
you wrote, that is the case.

997
00:59:45,205 --> 00:59:47,505
- What did he say?
- All fake?

998
00:59:47,505 --> 00:59:51,105
A coercive relationship,
urging an abortion, womanizing.

999
00:59:51,105 --> 00:59:56,172
I firmly state that none
of this ever happened.

1000
00:59:56,172 --> 00:59:57,338
But

1001
00:59:57,338 --> 00:59:59,972
it's true that

1002
00:59:59,972 --> 01:00:03,672
I have someone I love,

1003
01:00:05,538 --> 01:00:07,013
and that person is carrying my child.

1004
01:00:07,013 --> 01:00:08,805
- So that's true.
- Pregnant with his baby?

1005
01:00:08,805 --> 01:00:10,949
- You got that?
- The baby's real.

1006
01:00:15,472 --> 01:00:16,805
Are you admitting to a relationship

1007
01:00:16,805 --> 01:00:18,405
["The woman I truly love is pregnant"]
with a company employee now?

1008
01:00:18,405 --> 01:00:21,105
Are you saying that it's true
that the employee is pregnant?

1009
01:00:21,105 --> 01:00:22,138
Yes, that's correct.

1010
01:00:22,138 --> 01:00:24,505
How can you prove that you weren't

1011
01:00:24,505 --> 01:00:25,505
exploiting your position with her?

1012
01:00:25,505 --> 01:00:28,272
Just hearing that, I can't tell at all

1013
01:00:28,272 --> 01:00:31,872
whether you two are just
an ordinary couple or truly in love.

1014
01:00:43,105 --> 01:00:46,672
At first, she was a bit strange.

1015
01:00:46,672 --> 01:00:48,517
Here's grape juice...

1016
01:00:48,517 --> 01:00:50,821
No!

1017
01:00:52,069 --> 01:00:54,938
To the point where I never
wanted to see her again.

1018
01:00:54,938 --> 01:00:56,805
She was peculiar and intimidating.

1019
01:00:56,805 --> 01:00:58,772
- Did you get that?
- So she's real?

1020
01:00:58,772 --> 01:01:01,093
- Does he know what he's saying?
- We'll see.

1021
01:01:24,638 --> 01:01:26,372
But

1022
01:01:27,072 --> 01:01:29,972
we ended up meeting again.

1023
01:01:29,972 --> 01:01:32,338
And in an even more unexpected way.

1024
01:01:40,438 --> 01:01:42,705
From that moment,

1025
01:01:42,705 --> 01:01:45,705
I strangely became curious
about what she would do next.

1026
01:01:46,605 --> 01:01:47,872
That's when I made up my mind.

1027
01:01:47,872 --> 01:01:49,972
I've decided that I must
study in Germany next.

1028
01:01:49,972 --> 01:01:53,572
I've decided to create my own beer
that will captivate foreigners' taste buds.

1029
01:01:53,572 --> 01:01:54,738
That's my dream.

1030
01:01:54,738 --> 01:01:58,705
Especially, I envied the way
her eyes sparkled

1031
01:01:59,572 --> 01:02:01,305
when talking about beer.

1032
01:02:01,305 --> 01:02:02,905
So that's why you fell for her?

1033
01:02:02,905 --> 01:02:04,472
Is that all made up?

1034
01:02:04,472 --> 01:02:07,705
Honestly, until then, it was just curiosity.

1035
01:02:07,705 --> 01:02:10,738
Then when did you really start liking her?

1036
01:02:16,938 --> 01:02:19,205
When she said

1037
01:02:19,205 --> 01:02:20,905
she was giving up her dream.

1038
01:02:20,905 --> 01:02:25,838
I gave up my lifelong dream
with my own hands.

1039
01:02:25,838 --> 01:02:29,205
If I don't work now,
I feel like I'll actually die.

1040
01:02:29,205 --> 01:02:30,872
Please stop telling me to rest.

1041
01:02:30,872 --> 01:02:33,838
When the person who spoke of dreams

1042
01:02:33,838 --> 01:02:35,872
with such sparkling eyes
said she would give up,

1043
01:02:35,872 --> 01:02:38,205
I realized then.

1044
01:02:39,105 --> 01:02:41,038
That seeing her dream disappear

1045
01:02:41,038 --> 01:02:44,438
is sadder than my own dream being crushed.

1046
01:02:45,072 --> 01:02:46,805
That I

1047
01:02:51,405 --> 01:02:53,605
truly love her.

1048
01:02:54,484 --> 01:02:57,157
- He said he loves her!
- I don't know.

1049
01:03:07,941 --> 01:03:09,989
[Kang Du Jun denies forced abortion,
says he wanted to protect her]

1050
01:03:11,138 --> 01:03:12,872
You don't have to believe me.

1051
01:03:12,872 --> 01:03:16,805
Some may think these are just words
to get through this moment.

1052
01:03:16,805 --> 01:03:18,605
But the reason I'm saying this now

1053
01:03:18,605 --> 01:03:21,605
is because I don't want
that person to get hurt anymore.

1054
01:03:23,348 --> 01:03:25,445
- All of this is to protect her?
- It could be.

1055
01:03:36,605 --> 01:03:39,172
Let's talk about our next move immediately.

1056
01:03:39,172 --> 01:03:41,876
I'm leaving now.

1057
01:03:41,876 --> 01:03:42,938
That's unexpected...

1058
01:03:42,938 --> 01:03:46,505
She is really precious to me.

1059
01:03:46,505 --> 01:03:49,272
So I can't lie to deny her.

1060
01:03:49,272 --> 01:03:53,138
It's okay if you doubt me and criticize me.

1061
01:03:53,138 --> 01:03:57,372
But please refrain from excessive criticism

1062
01:03:58,238 --> 01:04:00,505
or speculation about them.

1063
01:04:01,172 --> 01:04:03,572
I sincerely request this.

1064
01:05:00,205 --> 01:05:01,472
That was impressive.

1065
01:05:01,472 --> 01:05:03,538
Please take good care of Hui Won.

1066
01:05:03,538 --> 01:05:04,538
What are you going to do now?

1067
01:05:04,538 --> 01:05:06,138
[Han Jeong Eum]
Do you have a backup plan?

1068
01:05:06,138 --> 01:05:09,305
The next heir of Taehan Group abused drugs,

1069
01:05:09,305 --> 01:05:11,872
even psychiatric medication.

1070
01:05:11,872 --> 01:05:15,138
You can't even manage a simple
handshake at official events.

1071
01:05:15,138 --> 01:05:18,238
Why not step down voluntarily at this point?

1072
01:05:18,238 --> 01:05:20,372
We have a new co-president at our company!

1073
01:05:20,372 --> 01:05:23,238
I explicitly told you not to mess with her.

1074
01:05:23,238 --> 01:05:24,838
Let's call the person in charge.

1075
01:05:24,838 --> 01:05:27,472
So you are really pregnant?

1076
01:05:27,472 --> 01:05:29,838
I'll step down if I must.
